{
  "texts": [
    "Further supporting this trend, Chi et al. [68] reported even greater reductions in workability, with drops of 15%, 25%, and 35% observed at replacement levels of 20%, 40%, and 60%.",
    "In contrast, Cleetus et al. [69] found that workability actually improved by 25% at a 20% GGBFS replacement level and by 40% at 40%, although a decrease in slump of 15-20% was noted at early stages.",
    "These findings suggest that the effects of GGBFS on concrete properties can vary widely depending on the specific conditions of use.",
    "Table 5 summarized studies that used GGBFS as SCMs and their effects on the concrete properties.",
    "MKOuldkhaoua et al. [71] and Jiang et al."
  ]
}